race.description: Sapphire Plaster Country Boosted Maiden Plate
race.comment: AIN'T SEEN MARS (7) brings solid form over a mile and will present at peak fitness. Has the inside barrier and the blinkers applied for the first time. Has been kept on the fresh side and a top rider is booked. I DOUBT IT (9)  finished 1.4 lengths from the winner last start after being prominent at the bend over 1650m at Moruya. Raced favourite and peaks today on an 8-day backup. Is ready to win and this is suitable. REVOKE (3) has been racing well without winning. Was a little plainer the latest but is worth another chance. AQUILINO (8) was outgraded at Randwick but the near miss at Queanbeyan prior over 1400m reads well enough. Draws low and has his first crack at the mile off a 36-day freshen. Consider. SHEER TERRA (11) is third-up and likely to show more.
